question.verify:
Sandbox JS calls env.opengrok.findFile("AuthService*");
If results.length > 1: calls env.opengrok.elicit() with enum of top file paths;
Handles action !== "accept" gracefully (returns cancellation message);
On accept: fetches and returns the selected file content.
If elicitation is unsupported, falls back to returning the first result with a note.

Sandbox JS calls env.opengrok.search("handelCrash");
totalCount === 0 triggers zero-result branch;
Checks result._suggestions first (may be auto-injected when sampling available);
Falls back to env.opengrok.sample() if _suggestions absent;
Returns "No results found. Try: <suggestions>" message;
Never crashes when sample() returns null (client sampling unsupported).
